    cellular: "SFBT emphasizes solutions rather than problems, future orientation rather than past exploration, and client strengths rather than deficits. Key techniques: miracle question (if the problem were solved overnight, what would be different?), exception-finding (when is the problem not occurring?), scaling questions (on a 1-10 scale, where are you?), coping questions (how have you managed?), and compliments. SFBT is typically 3-8 sessions. The therapist adopts a not-knowing stance, using the client's language and framework. SFBT is effective across diverse populations and settings including schools, child welfare, and brief therapy contexts.",
