    cellular: "Social determinants of health are the conditions in which people are born, grow, live, work, and age. They include economic stability, education, health access, neighborhood/environment, and social/community context. Poverty is the single strongest predictor of poor health outcomes. The ecological framework connects individual distress to structural factors. Social workers address SDH through micro (individual advocacy), mezzo (community programs), and macro (policy advocacy) interventions. Understanding systemic barriers prevents blaming individuals for structural problems. Community needs assessment identifies gaps in resources and services.",
