    title: "Community Resources and Case Management",
    cellular: "Case management connects clients with community resources to address comprehensive needs. Core functions: assessment, planning, linking, monitoring, and advocacy. Resources include housing assistance, food banks, healthcare access, employment services, childcare, legal aid, domestic violence shelters, substance abuse treatment, mental health services, and disability services. Social workers must maintain current knowledge of available community resources. Warm referrals (contacting the resource with the client) are more effective than cold referrals. Barriers to resource access include stigma, transportation, wait lists, eligibility criteria, and systemic racism.",
