    cellular: "The strengths-based perspective is a foundational social work approach focusing on client capabilities, resources, and resilience rather than deficits and pathology. Principles include: every individual, group, and community has strengths; trauma and struggle may also be sources of growth; take individual, group, and community aspirations seriously; collaboration is essential; and every environment contains resources. Assessment identifies strengths including personal qualities, talents, cultural/community resources, coping skills, support networks, and survival skills. Strengths-based practice does not ignore problems but addresses them through mobilizing existing capacities and resources.",
