    cellular: "Social workers in foster care and adoption facilitate placement, monitor child welfare, support families, and pursue permanency. Foster care types include traditional, therapeutic/specialized, kinship, and group home. Permanency goals in order of preference: reunification, adoption, guardianship, placement with fit relative, and APPLA (another planned permanent living arrangement). Adoption types include domestic infant, foster care, international, and stepparent. Social workers conduct home studies, provide pre-placement training, facilitate matching, support post-placement adjustment, and arrange post-adoption services. Attachment and grief issues are central to foster care and adoption work.",
